( breathing heavily )

1644
02:04:16.574 --> 02:04:19.577
( waves crashing )

1645
02:04:24.291 --> 02:04:26.334
You lost your cousin.

1646
02:04:26.376 --> 02:04:27.961
( blade rings under stone )

1647
02:04:28.002 --> 02:04:30.004
Now you've taken mine.

1648
02:04:32.340 --> 02:04:35.260
When does it end?

1649
02:04:36.886 --> 02:04:38.805
It never ends.

1650
02:04:47.605 --> 02:04:50.608
( waves rushing )

1651
02:04:59.242 --> 02:05:02.036
( waves receding )

1652
02:05:10.170 --> 02:05:12.172
( rustling )

1653
02:05:20.888 --> 02:05:23.141
( robe rustling )

1654
02:05:35.487 --> 02:05:37.071
Who are you?

1655
02:05:37.113 --> 02:05:40.950
I have endured
what no one on earth

1656
02:05:40.992 --> 02:05:43.786
has endured before.

1657
02:05:43.828 --> 02:05:49.667
I kissed the hands of the man
who killed my son.

1658
02:05:55.923 --> 02:05:57.591
Priam?

1659
02:05:59.260 --> 02:06:01.095
How did you get in here?

1660
02:06:01.137 --> 02:06:05.225
I know my own country better
than the Greeks, I think.

1661
02:06:09.770 --> 02:06:10.813
You're a brave man.

1662
02:06:15.026 --> 02:06:16.903
I could have your head on a spit

1663
02:06:16.944 --> 02:06:18.530
in the blink of an eye.

1664
02:06:18.612 --> 02:06:24.285
Do you really think death
frightens me now?

1665
02:06:24.327 --> 02:06:26.996
I watched my eldest son die,

1666
02:06:27.038 --> 02:06:31.918
watched you drag his body
behind your chariot.

1667
02:06:33.586 --> 02:06:36.630
Give him back to me.

1668
02:06:36.672 --> 02:06:39.717
He deserves the honor
of a proper burial.

1669
02:06:39.759 --> 02:06:42.178
You know that.

1670
02:06:42.220 --> 02:06:44.764
Give him to me.

1671
02:06:44.805 --> 02:06:46.891
He killed my cousin.

1672
02:06:46.933 --> 02:06:48.935
He thought it was you.

1673
02:06:51.354 --> 02:06:54.274
How many cousins
have you killed?

1674
02:06:55.691 --> 02:06:57.902
How many sons and fathers

1675
02:06:57.944 --> 02:06:59.904
and brothers and husbands?

1676
02:06:59.946 --> 02:07:04.367
How many,
brave Achilles?

1677
02:07:04.409 --> 02:07:07.579
I knew your father.

1678
02:07:07.619 --> 02:07:11.124
He died before his time.

1679
02:07:11.165 --> 02:07:13.709
But he was lucky
not to live long enough

1680
02:07:13.751 --> 02:07:16.588
to see his son fall.

1681
02:07:21.259 --> 02:07:26.347
You have taken
everything from me.

1682
02:07:26.389 --> 02:07:28.224
My eldest son,

1683
02:07:28.266 --> 02:07:30.518
heir to my throne,

1684
02:07:30.560 --> 02:07:34.439
defender of my kingdom.

1685
02:07:34.481 --> 02:07:37.233
I cannot change what happened.

1686
02:07:37.275 --> 02:07:40.194
It is the will of the gods.

1687
02:07:40.236 --> 02:07:44.698
But give me
this small mercy.

1688
02:07:44.740 --> 02:07:50.622
I loved my boy from the moment
he opened his eyes

1689
02:07:50.662 --> 02:07:53.958
till the moment you closed them.

1690
02:07:55.709 --> 02:08:00.173
Let me wash his body.

1691
02:08:00.214 --> 02:08:04.718
Let me say the prayers.

1692
02:08:04.760 --> 02:08:10.057
Let me place two coins
on his eyes for the boatman.

1693
02:08:13.436 --> 02:08:17.940
If I let you walk out of here...

1694
02:08:17.982 --> 02:08:18.941
( clears throat )

1695
02:08:18.983 --> 02:08:20.985
If I let you take him...

1696
02:08:23.613 --> 02:08:26.907
...it doesn't change anything.

1697
02:08:26.949 --> 02:08:30.286
You are still my enemy
in the morning.

1698
02:08:30.328 --> 02:08:35.124
You're still my enemy tonight.

1699
02:08:35.166 --> 02:08:39.753
But even enemies
can show respect.

1700
02:08:58.439 --> 02:09:00.107
I admire your courage.

1701
02:09:07.574 --> 02:09:09.534
Meet me outside in a moment.

1702
02:09:23.172 --> 02:09:27.385
( sobbing quietly )

1703
02:09:38.020 --> 02:09:40.022
( sniffling )

1704
02:09:52.285 --> 02:09:54.120
We'll meet again soon,
my brother.

1705
02:10:12.096 --> 02:10:15.642
Your son was the best
I've fought.

1706
02:10:15.683 --> 02:10:18.102
( sighs )

1707
02:10:18.144 --> 02:10:20.813
In my country, the funeral games
last for 12 days.

1708
02:10:20.854 --> 02:10:23.566
It is the same in my country.

1709
02:10:23.608 --> 02:10:25.735
Then the prince
will have that honor.

1710
02:10:25.777 --> 02:10:29.405
No Greek will attack Troy
for 12 days.

1711
02:10:35.495 --> 02:10:37.455
Briseis?

1712
02:10:37.497 --> 02:10:38.790
Oh!

1713
02:10:40.082 --> 02:10:41.751
We thought you
were dead.

1714
02:10:41.793 --> 02:10:43.503
We thought...

1715
02:10:52.845 --> 02:10:54.347
You're free.

1716
02:11:08.778 --> 02:11:10.404
If I hurt you...

1717
02:11:12.532 --> 02:11:14.908
it's not what I wanted.

1718
02:11:29.298 --> 02:11:30.882
Go.

1719
02:11:30.924 --> 02:11:35.012
No one will stop you.
You have my word.

1720
02:11:35.054 --> 02:11:37.097
Come, my girl.

1721
02:11:45.356 --> 02:11:46.733
You're a far
better king

1722
02:11:46.774 --> 02:11:49.151
than the one leading this army.

1723
02:11:51.487 --> 02:11:54.281
( chariot leaving )

1724
02:12:05.209 --> 02:12:08.755
Achilles makes a secret pact
and I have to honor it?

1725
02:12:08.796 --> 02:12:10.506
What treason is this?

1726
02:12:10.548 --> 02:12:12.592
Consorting with the enemy king.

1727
02:12:12.633 --> 02:12:17.012
Giving him 12 days of peace.
Peace! Peace!

1728
02:12:17.054 --> 02:12:20.224
Their prince is dead,
their army is leaderless.

1729
02:12:20.266 --> 02:12:21.975
This is the time to attack!

1730
02:12:22.017 --> 02:12:26.146
Even with Hector gone, we have
no way to breach their walls.

1731
02:12:26.188 --> 02:12:28.858
I will smash their walls
to the ground

1732
02:12:28.900 --> 02:12:32.152
if it costs me 40,000 Greeks.

1733
02:12:32.194 --> 02:12:34.029
Hear me, Zeus!

1734
02:12:34.071 --> 02:12:39.243
I will smash their walls
to the ground!

1735
02:12:39.285 --> 02:12:40.661
( sighs )

1736
02:12:52.172 --> 02:12:53.716
It's good.

1737
02:12:53.758 --> 02:12:55.676
For my son back home.

1738
02:13:19.951 --> 02:13:23.788
AGAMEMNON:
Well, Odysseus.

1739
02:13:23.830 --> 02:13:26.039
You found a way
to make the sheep

1740
02:13:26.081 --> 02:13:28.835
invite the wolves to dinner.

1741
02:13:43.975 --> 02:13:46.101
Forgive me, Eudorus.

1742
02:13:46.143 --> 02:13:48.020
I should never have struck you.

1743
02:13:48.061 --> 02:13:53.776
You've been a loyal friend
all your life.

1744
02:13:53.818 --> 02:13:56.779
I hope I never
disappoint you again.

1745
02:13:56.821 --> 02:14:00.783
It's I who have been
the disappointment.

1746
02:14:00.825 --> 02:14:03.786
Rouse the men,
you're taking them home.

1747
02:14:03.828 --> 02:14:06.580
Aren't you coming with us?

1748
02:14:06.622 --> 02:14:09.542
I have my own battle
to fight.

1749
02:14:09.583 --> 02:14:11.126
Then we march beside you.

1750
02:14:11.168 --> 02:14:12.586
No.

1751
02:14:12.628 --> 02:14:15.381
I don't want our men
to be a part of this.

1752
02:14:21.470 --> 02:14:23.305
It's a beautiful night.

1753
02:14:23.347 --> 02:14:24.431
Go, Eudorus.

1754
02:14:24.473 --> 02:14:27.267
This is the last order
I give you.

1755
02:14:32.523 --> 02:14:34.859
Fighting for you has been
my life's honor, my lord.

1756
02:14:45.995 --> 02:14:49.373
♪ ♪

1757
02:15:12.563 --> 02:15:15.566
♪ ♪

1758
02:15:38.297 --> 02:15:41.258
♪ ♪

1759
02:15:45.930 --> 02:15:49.892
Open the gates! Open the gates!

1760
02:15:52.853 --> 02:15:55.272
( horses neighing )

1761
02:16:01.612 --> 02:16:03.864
GLAUCUS:
Here.

1762
02:16:29.140 --> 02:16:30.599
PRIAM:
Plague.

1763
02:16:32.225 --> 02:16:34.269
GLAUCUS:
Don't get too close, my king.

1764
02:16:34.311 --> 02:16:36.730
This is the will
of the gods.

1765
02:16:36.772 --> 02:16:39.775
They desecrated
the temple of Apollo,

1766
02:16:39.817 --> 02:16:42.778
and Apollo desecrated
their flesh.

1767
02:16:42.820 --> 02:16:44.155
They thought they
could come here

1768
02:16:44.237 --> 02:16:46.699
and sack our city
in a day.

1769
02:16:46.740 --> 02:16:50.953
Now look at them,
fleeing across the Aegean.

1770
02:16:54.123 --> 02:16:55.916
PRIAM:
What is this?

1771
02:16:55.958 --> 02:16:58.711
ARCHEPTOLEMUS:
An offering to Poseidon.

1772
02:16:58.752 --> 02:17:02.048
The Greeks are praying
for a safe return home.

1773
02:17:02.089 --> 02:17:03.549
This is a gift.

1774
02:17:03.590 --> 02:17:06.343
We should take it
to the temple of Poseidon.

1775
02:17:06.385 --> 02:17:07.970
I think we should burn it.

1776
02:17:08.012 --> 02:17:09.096
VELIOR:
Burn it?

1777
02:17:09.138 --> 02:17:11.222
My prince,
it's a gift to the gods.

1778
02:17:14.101 --> 02:17:17.354
Father, burn it.

1779
02:17:18.856 --> 02:17:22.776
( shouts and cheers )

1780
02:17:31.118 --> 02:17:33.328
( loud rumbling )

1781
02:17:40.502 --> 02:17:43.089
( grunting )

1782
02:17:43.130 --> 02:17:45.716
( shouting and cheering )

1783
02:18:08.488 --> 02:18:11.242
( cheering )

1784
02:18:14.536 --> 02:18:16.080
PARIS:
Look at them.

1785
02:18:17.915 --> 02:18:19.917
You'd think their
prince had never died.

1786
02:18:22.377 --> 02:18:25.422
You're their prince now.

1787
02:18:25.464 --> 02:18:28.217
Make your brother proud.

1788
02:18:44.399 --> 02:18:46.485
( neighing )

1789
02:18:46.526 --> 02:18:48.279
( grunts )

1790
02:19:10.425 --> 02:19:13.637
♪ ♪

1791
02:19:23.814 --> 02:19:26.025
♪ ♪

1792
02:19:35.575 --> 02:19:38.329
♪ ♪

1793
02:19:43.834 --> 02:19:45.919
( grunts )

1794
02:19:47.838 --> 02:19:49.798
( groaning )

1795
02:20:00.184 --> 02:20:01.852
♪ ♪

1796
02:20:37.137 --> 02:20:39.472
♪ ♪

1797
02:20:42.935 --> 02:20:45.604
( muffled yelling )

1798
02:20:55.072 --> 02:20:57.408
( muffled screaming )

1799
02:21:04.706 --> 02:21:07.626
♪ ♪

1800
02:21:31.108 --> 02:21:33.735
( muffled screaming )

1801
02:21:42.035 --> 02:21:44.663
( shouting )

1802
02:21:53.672 --> 02:21:56.633
( shouts and screams )

1803
02:22:04.808 --> 02:22:06.018
Briseis. Where is she?

1804
02:22:06.810 --> 02:22:07.560
Where?

1805
02:22:07.602 --> 02:22:09.104
I don't know.

1806
02:22:09.146 --> 02:22:11.106
Please, I have a son.

1807
02:22:11.148 --> 02:22:13.317
Then get him out of Troy.

1808
02:22:16.778 --> 02:22:20.073
( neighing )

1809
02:22:29.333 --> 02:22:30.834
Briseis!

1810
02:22:36.548 --> 02:22:39.676
( screaming )

1811
02:22:48.643 --> 02:22:51.438
( indistinct shouting )

1812
02:22:59.738 --> 02:23:02.866
( distant screaming )

1813
02:23:14.711 --> 02:23:17.714
Paris! Andromache!

1814
02:23:19.383 --> 02:23:21.843
Helen, we must go.
Where?

1815
02:23:21.885 --> 02:23:23.512
I'll show you.
Now! Hurry!

1816
02:23:23.554 --> 02:23:24.637
Paris, Paris...

1817
02:23:24.679 --> 02:23:25.847
ANDROMACHE:
It's a long way.

1818
02:23:25.889 --> 02:23:27.766
Quick. We must go now.

1819
02:23:27.807 --> 02:23:29.268
Briseis!

1820
02:23:32.312 --> 02:23:33.355
BRISEIS:
Paris!

1821
02:23:38.485 --> 02:23:40.653
( gasps )

1822
02:23:47.578 --> 02:23:51.873
Let it burn! Let Troy burn!

1823
02:23:51.915 --> 02:23:55.835
Burn it! Burn it all!

1824
02:23:55.877 --> 02:23:58.088
Burn Troy!

1825
02:23:58.130 --> 02:24:00.840
Burn Troy!

1826
02:24:00.882 --> 02:24:03.552
It's a long way. Quick.

1827
02:24:03.594 --> 02:24:06.221
( indistinct shouting )

1828
02:24:07.473 --> 02:24:08.890
Come.
I stay.

1829
02:24:08.932 --> 02:24:10.100
No.

1830
02:24:10.142 --> 02:24:11.893
My father will never
abandon the city.

1831
02:24:11.935 --> 02:24:12.894
I can't leave him.

1832
02:24:12.936 --> 02:24:14.396
The city is dead.

1833
02:24:14.438 --> 02:24:16.356
They're burning it
to the ground.

1834
02:24:16.398 --> 02:24:18.400
( indistinct mumbling )

1835
02:24:18.442 --> 02:24:19.401
What's your name?

1836
02:24:19.443 --> 02:24:20.652
Aeneas.

1837
02:24:20.693 --> 02:24:21.987
Do you know how
to use a sword?

1838
02:24:22.028 --> 02:24:23.738
Yes.

1839
02:24:23.780 --> 02:24:25.782
The sword of Troy.

1840
02:24:25.824 --> 02:24:27.867
As long as it remains
in the hands of a Trojan,

1841
02:24:27.909 --> 02:24:29.035
our people have a future.

1842
02:24:29.077 --> 02:24:30.662
Protect them, Aeneas.

1843
02:24:30.703 --> 02:24:31.913
Find them a new home.

1844
02:24:31.955 --> 02:24:33.248
I will.

1845
02:24:33.290 --> 02:24:34.707
ANDROMACHE:
Hurry! Quick!

1846
02:24:34.749 --> 02:24:37.710
Paris, Paris, Briseis
wasn't in her room.

1847
02:24:37.752 --> 02:24:39.087
I'll find her.

1848
02:24:41.465 --> 02:24:42.924
Go.

1849
02:24:44.009 --> 02:24:44.968
I'll stay with you.

1850
02:24:45.010 --> 02:24:45.760
Go.

1851
02:24:45.802 --> 02:24:47.053
Please don't leave me.

1852
02:24:47.095 --> 02:24:49.097
How could you love
me if I ran now?

1853
02:24:49.139 --> 02:24:49.889
Please.

1854
02:24:49.931 --> 02:24:51.099
We will be together again,

1855
02:24:51.141 --> 02:24:52.767
in this world or the next.

1856
02:24:52.809 --> 02:24:53.893
We will be together.

1857
02:25:00.233 --> 02:25:01.985
Go.

1858
02:25:05.155 --> 02:25:06.948
To the gates!

1859
02:25:06.990 --> 02:25:08.825
( grunting )

1860
02:25:11.328 --> 02:25:13.497
( yelling )

1861
02:25:15.748 --> 02:25:17.250
( shouting )

1862
02:25:17.292 --> 02:25:18.960
( grunting )

1863
02:25:19.002 --> 02:25:21.129
Soldiers of Troy,

1864
02:25:21.171 --> 02:25:23.507
you men are warriors!

1865
02:25:23.549 --> 02:25:26.593
To lead you has been my honor!

1866
02:25:26.635 --> 02:25:27.594
( cheering )

1867
02:25:27.636 --> 02:25:28.887
My prince!

1868
02:25:28.928 --> 02:25:30.763
( banging )

1869
02:25:30.805 --> 02:25:32.974
The boatman waits for us.

1870
02:25:33.016 --> 02:25:36.936
I say we make him
wait a little longer!

1871
02:25:38.647 --> 02:25:40.232
( shouting )

1872
02:25:45.862 --> 02:25:46.946
( screams )

1873
02:25:51.702 --> 02:25:53.704
( grunting )

1874
02:25:53.745 --> 02:25:56.789
( metal clanging )

1875
02:25:58.458 --> 02:26:00.168
BRISEIS:
Paris!

1876
02:26:00.210 --> 02:26:01.628
Paris!

1877
02:26:03.796 --> 02:26:06.550
( grunting )

1878
02:26:11.054 --> 02:26:12.723
( shouting )

1879
02:26:15.475 --> 02:26:18.353
( shouting )

1880
02:26:29.197 --> 02:26:31.908
( shouting )

1881
02:26:37.414 --> 02:26:40.875
Have you no honor?!

1882
02:26:40.917 --> 02:26:43.629
Have
you no honor?!

1883
02:26:43.670 --> 02:26:45.505
( grunts )

1884
02:26:49.593 --> 02:26:51.886
( grunts )

1885
02:26:57.517 --> 02:27:01.480
( groans )

1886
02:27:01.521 --> 02:27:05.317
( women screaming )

1887
02:27:14.825 --> 02:27:17.912
Too late for prayer, priestess.

1888
02:27:17.954 --> 02:27:22.125
( grunting, groaning )

1889
02:27:25.295 --> 02:27:29.466
I almost lost this war because
of your little romance.

1890
02:27:29.508 --> 02:27:32.385
( screaming )

1891
02:27:40.602 --> 02:27:44.189
You'll be my slave

1892
02:27:44.230 --> 02:27:45.607
in Mycenae.

1893
02:27:45.649 --> 02:27:50.861
A Trojan priestess
scrubbing my floors.

1894
02:27:50.903 --> 02:27:53.406
And at night...

1895
02:27:53.448 --> 02:27:55.784
( gasping )

1896
02:27:56.743 --> 02:27:58.036
( screaming )

1897
02:27:58.077 --> 02:28:02.415
( choking gasps )

1898
02:28:04.668 --> 02:28:06.795
( grunts )

1899
02:28:06.837 --> 02:28:09.130
Get up!

1900
02:28:11.717 --> 02:28:12.676
Hold her.

1901
02:28:15.345 --> 02:28:17.138
( grunting )

1902
02:28:21.727 --> 02:28:23.019
Come with me.

1903
02:28:26.732 --> 02:28:27.440
No!

1904
02:28:29.359 --> 02:28:31.737
( gasping )

1905
02:28:33.154 --> 02:28:35.699
Paris!

1906
02:28:40.537 --> 02:28:41.454
No!

1907
02:28:41.496 --> 02:28:43.832
( grunts )

1908
02:28:46.125 --> 02:28:47.753
( groans )

1909
02:28:52.006 --> 02:28:53.174
Don't!

1910
02:28:53.216 --> 02:28:55.218
Please!

1911
02:28:59.806 --> 02:29:02.851
Paris! Don't!

1912
02:29:05.061 --> 02:29:06.229
( groans )

1913
02:29:16.239 --> 02:29:18.617
( grunts )

1914
02:29:28.835 --> 02:29:30.336
It's all right.

1915
02:29:30.378 --> 02:29:33.005
It's all
right.

1916
02:29:45.059 --> 02:29:47.562
( sniffling )

